The following directions apply for openSuSE 11.2:

Note the following conventions. A '#' at the beginning of a line means execute
as root, while a '$' means execute as normal user.

Install requirements to run our Django project:
-----------------------------------------------
# zypper addrepo http://download.opensuse.org/repositories/devel:/languages:/python/openSUSE_11.2 python
# zypper install python-setuptools python-django
# easy_install django-registration rpc4django

Test Django Application:
------------------------
$ cd <egeni_root>/v2/src/python/clearinghouse
$ python manage.py runserver

Point your browser to localhost:8000 to make sure Django works. Kill the server.

Setup Apache2 to use SSL:
-------------------------
# zypper addrepo http://download.opensuse.org/repositories/Apache:/Modules/openSUSE_11.2/ Apache:Modules
# zypper install apache2 apache2-mod_wsgi
# sed -i '{s/APACHE_CONF_INCLUDE_FILES=""/APACHE_CONF_INCLUDE_FILES="/etc/apache2/httpd.conf.local"/}' /etc/sysconfig/apache2
# cp <egeni_root>/v2/src/config/apache/httpd.conf.local /etc/apache2/
# sed -i '{s/egeni_root/<actual_egeni_root>/}' /etc/apache2/httpd.conf.local
# cp <egeni_root>/v2/src/config/apache/vhost-ssl.conf /etc/apache2/vhosts.d/
# a2enmod ssl
# a2enflag SSL
# /usr/bin/gensslcert
# sed -i '{s/Listen 80/#Listen 80/}' /etc/apache2/listen.conf
# /etc/init.d/apache2 restart

Point your browser to https://localhost/ to make sure SSL works.
